---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { skills, education } from '../data/site';
---

<PageLayout title="About - Chandran Nandkumar" description="Robotics and AI engineer focused on trustworthy embodied intelligence.">
  <section class="container page-top about-hero">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="page-title">Researcher-builder for<br /><em>embodied intelligence.</em></h1>
    </div>
    <div class="bio">
      <p>
        I am a robotics and AI engineer with an MSc in Robotics from <strong>TU Delft</strong> and a
        mechanical engineering foundation from <strong>NITK Surathkal</strong>. I recently accepted a
        rapid prototyping role at <strong>Lely</strong>, after working at <strong>Qafka Robotics</strong> on
        real-world autonomy for a mobile robot in an industrial port environment.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most of my work circles the same question from different angles: how do humans work with
        intelligent systems that are too complex to fully reason about? At TU Delft, that meant
        conversational interfaces for robots. At Qafka, it became perception, control, state
        machines, embedded actuation, and the reality that robots fail at subsystem boundaries.
      </p>
      <p>
        The thread is now clearer: trustworthy embodied intelligence. I want to build systems that
        make robot policies more interpretable, steerable, reliable, and easier for humans to
        supervise, without pretending that autonomy becomes safe just because the demo works once.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container kit">
    <div class="kit-col">
      <span class="eyebrow">Focus</span>
      <ul class="kit-list">
        {skills.focus.map((f) => <li>{f}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="kit-col">
      <span class="eyebrow">Software & platforms</span>
      <div class="tag-row">
        {skills.software.map((s) => <span class="tag">{s}</span>)}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="kit-col">
      <span class="eyebrow">Strengths</span>
      <ul class="kit-list">
        {skills.competencies.map((c) => <li>{c}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container edu">
    <span class="eyebrow">Education</span>
    {education.map((e) => (
      <div class="edu-row">
        <h2 class="edu-school">{e.school}</h2>
        <p class="edu-degree">{e.degree}</p>
        <span class="edu-years">{e.years}</span>
      </div>
    ))}
  </section>

  <section class="section container cta-band">
    <h2 class="section-title">Want to talk robotics, autonomy, or interpretability?</h2>
    <a class="pill" href="/contact">Get in touch →</a>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(28px, 5vw, 80px); align-items: start; padding-bottom: clamp(40px, 6vh, 80px); }
  .page-title { margin-top: 18px; }
  .bio p { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 18px; font-size: var(--text-lg); }
  .bio strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 500; }

  .kit { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: clamp(28px, 4vw, 64px); }
  .kit-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: grid; gap: 12px; }
  .kit-list li { padding-left: 20px; position: relative; line-height: 1.4; }
  .kit-list li::before { content: '—'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-accent); }

  .edu-row { padding: 22px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .edu-row:first-of-type { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-top: 24px; }
  .edu-school { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 1rem + 1vw, 1.9rem); }
  .edu-degree { color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 8px; }
  .edu-years { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: 8px; display: inline-block; }

  .cta-band { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .kit { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
